<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="enough-adv">enough <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɪ'nʌf/    美 /ɪ'nʌf/  </p>
<p>[用于动词、形容词、副词之后]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>足够地；充分地：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He knows the situation well enough. 
他对情况了如指掌。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I became confident enough to challenge the good tennis players. 
我变得足够有信心去挑战好的网球选手了。</p><footer>2013 浙江</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They were not calm enough and both said some really mean things.
他们俩都不够冷静，都说了一些刻薄的话。</p><footer>2012 江苏书面表达</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is old enough to look after his younger sister.
他长大了，能照看妹妹了。</p></div></div>